1
00:00:11,125 --> 00:00:12,458
Okay, this sucks.

2
00:00:13,500 --> 00:00:14,416
Yeah.

3
00:00:19,166 --> 00:00:21,208
So, you're sure
we're locked in, right?

4
00:00:21,291 --> 00:00:22,208
Yup.

5
00:00:23,250 --> 00:00:25,916
That's it. I'll just have
to break the door down.

6
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:27,500
Stand back for a sec.

7
00:00:27,583 --> 00:00:31,041
Wait, not yet.
Isn't that a burglar alarm?

8
00:00:32,083 --> 00:00:34,833
If you damage the door,
the security guards might come.

9
00:00:36,708 --> 00:00:38,041
[FUTARO] Great, that'll mean
we get out of here

10
00:00:38,125 --> 00:00:39,375
that much faster!

11
00:00:39,458 --> 00:00:41,833
Hold on, let's think
about this!

12
00:00:41,916 --> 00:00:44,583
Something like that could get
the whole school sent home!

13
00:00:47,166 --> 00:00:50,500
Besides, if Miku found out
we were in here.

14
00:00:50,583 --> 00:00:54,000
♪

15
00:00:54,083 --> 00:00:57,125
Fine then.
Maybe you can disarm it.

16
00:00:57,208 --> 00:00:59,375
Hmm?
[giggles]

17
00:00:59,458 --> 00:01:01,875
Yeah, sure I could,
if I was like ten feet tall.

18
00:01:01,958 --> 00:01:03,708
Don't be absurd.

19
00:01:03,791 --> 00:01:06,041
Come over here.
I'll help you up.

20
00:01:06,125 --> 00:01:09,958
♪

21
00:01:10,041 --> 00:01:14,750
[heartbeat thumping]

22
00:01:14,833 --> 00:01:17,875
[ICHIKA] Stay calm.
Forget the burglar alarm.

23
00:01:17,958 --> 00:01:20,250
My heart's beating
even louder than that!

24
00:01:20,333 --> 00:01:24,000
♪

25
00:01:24,083 --> 00:01:25,750
You better not say I'm heavy.

26
00:01:27,500 --> 00:01:29,541
-You okay?
-[FUTARO] Yeah.

27
00:01:29,625 --> 00:01:30,791
Here goes.

28
00:01:33,541 --> 00:01:36,708
-[ICHIKA] Um, what's wrong?
-This feels familiar.

29
00:01:37,708 --> 00:01:39,541
Have I been here before?

30
00:01:39,625 --> 00:01:41,750
Hey, this is no time
for you to enjoy

31
00:01:41,833 --> 00:01:43,125
how great my thighs are!

32
00:01:43,208 --> 00:01:45,291
True, I'm about
to be squished by your weight!

33
00:01:45,375 --> 00:01:46,958
[ICHIKA]
Excuse me?

34
00:01:47,041 --> 00:01:48,583
What did I just say?

35
00:03:19,041 --> 00:03:22,958
♪

36
00:03:23,041 --> 00:03:24,750
If we don't want
to get in trouble,

37
00:03:24,833 --> 00:03:26,416
we have to turn
that sensor off.

38
00:03:26,500 --> 00:03:27,583
[BOTH straining]

39
00:03:27,666 --> 00:03:28,833
FUTARO]
Never mind, let's just wait.

40
00:03:28,916 --> 00:03:30,083
[screams in pain]

41
00:03:30,166 --> 00:03:32,333
I have a question, teach.

42
00:03:32,416 --> 00:03:34,541
What is it you're
doing over there?

43
00:03:34,625 --> 00:03:36,500
I'm making a fire, of course.

44
00:03:37,791 --> 00:03:40,125
Camp won't be fun
if we catch cold.

45
00:03:41,541 --> 00:03:44,833
For a smart guy, he can be
pretty stupid sometimes.

46
00:03:45,916 --> 00:03:47,041
Well, there's nothing to do,

47
00:03:47,125 --> 00:03:48,625
so let's talk about
something fun.

48
00:03:48,708 --> 00:03:50,875
Not right now.
I'm trying to focus on this.

49
00:03:56,333 --> 00:03:58,458
I can't believe
Ichika's not back yet.

50
00:03:58,541 --> 00:04:00,041
[ITSUKI]
Yeah.

51
00:04:00,125 --> 00:04:02,041
She said she had a few things
to do for the campfire,

52
00:04:02,125 --> 00:04:03,625
but that was a while ago.

53
00:04:03,708 --> 00:04:06,458
[YOTSUBA]
Miku! Itsuki!

54
00:04:06,541 --> 00:04:08,875
Have either of you
seen Uesugi anywhere?

55
00:04:09,958 --> 00:04:11,541
It's the weirdest thing!

56
00:04:11,625 --> 00:04:13,833
He was helping the campfire
group with our chores,

57
00:04:13,916 --> 00:04:16,458
and now I can't
figure out where he is!

58
00:04:16,541 --> 00:04:18,500
I checked the room
and the dining hall!

59
00:04:18,583 --> 00:04:19,875
He's just gone!

60
00:04:20,916 --> 00:04:23,958
He probably wandered off
to study or something!

61
00:04:26,291 --> 00:04:28,166
[ICHIKA] Are you sure
you're okay with that?

62
00:04:29,291 --> 00:04:32,041
Well, I'll try to look
after him then.

63
00:04:32,125 --> 00:04:34,125
Just leave it
to your oldest sister.

64
00:04:36,291 --> 00:04:38,875
Be right back.
I'm gonna go look!

65
00:04:38,958 --> 00:04:40,291
Wait, Miku!

66
00:04:43,250 --> 00:04:44,791
[ITSUKI]
What's that key for, Yotsuba?

67
00:04:47,291 --> 00:04:49,083
[ICHIKA] Oh, you'll get
a kick out of this!

68
00:04:50,416 --> 00:04:52,125
The other day,
Itsuki was like...

69
00:04:53,416 --> 00:04:56,291
So, that wasn't good for Nino.

70
00:04:56,375 --> 00:04:59,333
And as soon as she saw
that croquette, she was all...

71
00:04:59,416 --> 00:05:01,333
Ugh, never mind.

72
00:05:02,750 --> 00:05:04,708
Not one peep.

73
00:05:04,791 --> 00:05:06,916
You're gonna make
Big Sis cry again.

74
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:14,541
He still hasn't asked me
why I cried, though.

75
00:05:15,541 --> 00:05:17,333
Maybe he doesn't care.

76
00:05:18,333 --> 00:05:21,250
I mean, why did I, anyway?

77
00:05:21,333 --> 00:05:22,750
♪

78
00:05:26,833 --> 00:05:29,666
I think I might quit school.

79
00:05:32,333 --> 00:05:33,416
Wha...

80
00:05:35,708 --> 00:05:37,625
I knew that would get
your attention.

81
00:05:38,625 --> 00:05:40,708
Are you being serious
right now?

82
00:05:40,791 --> 00:05:43,458
Technically, I would
just be taking a break.

83
00:05:45,416 --> 00:05:46,791
Okay. Cool!

84
00:05:47,958 --> 00:05:50,625
[MAN] And cut!
Nice work, Ichika.

85
00:05:52,541 --> 00:05:54,500
[ICHIKA]
So, you know how I've been busy

86
00:05:54,583 --> 00:05:55,875
filming this new movie, right?

87
00:05:56,916 --> 00:05:58,625
I'm starting to get
more work now.

88
00:05:58,708 --> 00:06:00,750
My career's really
been taking off.

89
00:06:01,833 --> 00:06:04,333
Usually, actors my age
take a year off of school

90
00:06:04,416 --> 00:06:05,833
when they have a big project.

91
00:06:05,916 --> 00:06:07,000
Or they move to a school

92
00:06:07,083 --> 00:06:08,708
that has
a more flexible schedule.

93
00:06:09,708 --> 00:06:11,083
And come on, we both know that

94
00:06:11,166 --> 00:06:13,541
there isn't much of a future
for me in academics.

95
00:06:14,666 --> 00:06:17,333
I'm pretty sure
I won't miss school at all, heh.

96
00:06:18,625 --> 00:06:22,166
Besides, Miku might be
better off that way.

97
00:06:22,250 --> 00:06:23,208
[wood scraping]

98
00:06:25,166 --> 00:06:27,000
[FUTARO]
That's good.

99
00:06:27,083 --> 00:06:29,083
You found something
that you want to do.

100
00:06:30,291 --> 00:06:31,791
Fine by me.

101
00:06:31,875 --> 00:06:34,250
Wait! What happens to my pay
if you drop out of school?

102
00:06:34,333 --> 00:06:35,833
I'm out twenty percent!

103
00:06:35,916 --> 00:06:36,791
[ICHIKA sighs]

104
00:06:36,875 --> 00:06:39,583
Your reaction surprised me.

105
00:06:39,666 --> 00:06:41,083
[FUTARO]
You fail at life!

106
00:06:41,166 --> 00:06:43,291
[ICHIKA]
I expected a full rampage.

107
00:06:43,375 --> 00:06:45,875
Is that how you see me,
as some big tyrant?

108
00:06:45,958 --> 00:06:49,625
♪

109
00:06:49,708 --> 00:06:51,000
[ICHIKA]
Tell me, Futaro.

110
00:06:51,083 --> 00:06:53,166
What's the real reason
you study?

111
00:06:54,875 --> 00:06:57,625
Truth is, I kind of envy you
for having options.

112
00:06:59,291 --> 00:07:02,333
Well, there's still a 99 percent
chance that you'll fail.

113
00:07:02,416 --> 00:07:03,958
That sounds like you!

114
00:07:04,041 --> 00:07:05,791
[FUTARO] I think it'll be
a good experience.

115
00:07:06,875 --> 00:07:08,875
And if it works out,
that's great.

116
00:07:09,958 --> 00:07:11,458
It's worth a shot.

117
00:07:11,541 --> 00:07:12,541
Most things are.

118
00:07:17,375 --> 00:07:20,375
-Futaro?
-Ichika?

119
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:28,666
[ITSUKI] I wonder
if the two of them are...

120
00:07:32,041 --> 00:07:33,708
[MIKU]
It'll be okay.

121
00:07:34,791 --> 00:07:35,958
[ITSUKI]
Miku.

122
00:07:37,291 --> 00:07:38,875
It's fine if he's with Ichika.

123
00:07:39,875 --> 00:07:42,333
[crackling]

124
00:07:42,416 --> 00:07:46,291
♪

125
00:07:46,375 --> 00:07:47,875
-I don't mind.
-Huh?

126
00:07:49,208 --> 00:07:51,291
You know,
about the campfire dance.

127
00:07:53,125 --> 00:07:54,583
You're right,
it's probably better

128
00:07:54,666 --> 00:07:56,291
if we call the whole thing off.

129
00:07:57,750 --> 00:07:59,583
Oh.

130
00:07:59,666 --> 00:08:01,166
But hey, I've got an idea.

131
00:08:02,208 --> 00:08:06,625
♪

132
00:08:06,708 --> 00:08:08,333
We can dance now.

133
00:08:09,500 --> 00:08:12,291
I mean, we even have
our own private campfire!

134
00:08:12,375 --> 00:08:16,041
♪

135
00:08:16,125 --> 00:08:18,125
[FUTARO]
Sure. Not like anyone's looking.

136
00:08:18,208 --> 00:08:19,500
All right!

137
00:08:20,500 --> 00:08:22,958
I knew it, you were embarrassed!

138
00:08:23,041 --> 00:08:24,083
Obviously.

139
00:08:24,166 --> 00:08:26,083
That's so adorable.

140
00:08:28,833 --> 00:08:32,208
[heartbeat thumping]

141
00:08:32,291 --> 00:08:35,083
I can do this without
my heartbeat giving me away.

142
00:08:36,416 --> 00:08:39,375
I mean, it's awkward enough
without this whole legend thing.

143
00:08:39,458 --> 00:08:41,708
People would make assumptions.

144
00:08:43,750 --> 00:08:44,833
Wait, legend?

145
00:08:45,875 --> 00:08:47,291
Oh, you didn't know?

146
00:08:47,375 --> 00:08:48,833
I heard about it from Yotsuba.

147
00:08:48,916 --> 00:08:50,833
It says if you dance
with someone at the campfire,

148
00:08:50,916 --> 00:08:52,166
you'll be together for life.

149
00:08:52,250 --> 00:08:53,666
[gasps]

150
00:08:55,458 --> 00:08:56,458
[ICHIKA]
Oh.

151
00:08:57,500 --> 00:08:59,125
Does Miku know that?

152
00:08:59,208 --> 00:09:01,500
Yeah. She was there too.

153
00:09:06,041 --> 00:09:08,375
Oh no, I wasn't trying
to interfere.

154
00:09:10,666 --> 00:09:12,000
[FUTARO]
What's wrong?

155
00:09:13,000 --> 00:09:16,333
She wanted this so badly.

156
00:09:17,875 --> 00:09:19,416
And I took it away.

157
00:09:21,291 --> 00:09:22,333
Look, Futaro!

158
00:09:23,625 --> 00:09:25,000
[creaking]

159
00:09:26,000 --> 00:09:26,958
Watch out!

160
00:09:28,791 --> 00:09:29,750
[gasps]

161
00:09:30,791 --> 00:09:31,875
[FUTARO grunts]

162
00:09:41,541 --> 00:09:44,000
Whew. That was close.

163
00:09:44,083 --> 00:09:45,375
Jeez, Ichika.

164
00:09:46,750 --> 00:09:48,291
You're pretty clumsy, huh?

165
00:09:49,833 --> 00:09:53,333
[heartbeat thumping rapidly]

166
00:09:55,333 --> 00:09:59,333
[alarm blaring]

167
00:10:05,958 --> 00:10:07,666
Hey, let go of me!

168
00:10:07,750 --> 00:10:09,083
I'm trying to!

169
00:10:09,166 --> 00:10:10,916
[BOTH scream]

170
00:10:11,000 --> 00:10:12,708
[electronic voice]
Disturbance detected.

171
00:10:12,791 --> 00:10:15,166
Please unlock
within thirty seconds.

172
00:10:16,916 --> 00:10:20,125
If system is not disarmed,
security will be alerted.

173
00:10:21,125 --> 00:10:23,666
Not good.
We gotta get outta here now!

174
00:10:23,750 --> 00:10:24,750
[ICHIKA]
Yeah!

175
00:10:26,166 --> 00:10:28,166
-[screams]
-What the hell is this crap?

176
00:10:28,250 --> 00:10:30,875
Sprinklers, duh!
In case of fire!

177
00:10:30,958 --> 00:10:33,125
Let's stop the sensor first.

178
00:10:33,208 --> 00:10:35,000
But how do we do that?

179
00:10:35,083 --> 00:10:36,833
Aren't we supposed
to use the key?

180
00:10:36,916 --> 00:10:39,541
Key? It's never simple.

181
00:10:41,500 --> 00:10:42,416
[alarm stops]

182
00:10:42,500 --> 00:10:43,666
-Huh?
-Huh?

183
00:10:44,791 --> 00:10:46,750
[ITSUKI] The key was sitting
right outside.

184
00:10:51,791 --> 00:10:52,791
Ichika.

185
00:10:53,916 --> 00:10:55,833
So, this is where you've been.

186
00:10:55,916 --> 00:10:57,333
What were you guys doing?

187
00:11:08,791 --> 00:11:12,541
♪

188
00:11:12,625 --> 00:11:14,416
It's the last day of camp.

189
00:11:15,958 --> 00:11:18,291
I had to explain the shed
incident to the teachers.

190
00:11:18,375 --> 00:11:20,166
We both got in serious trouble.

191
00:11:21,291 --> 00:11:24,458
Itsuki and Miku were skeptical.

192
00:11:24,541 --> 00:11:27,208
I hope I get another chance
to tell them nothing happened.

193
00:11:28,583 --> 00:11:31,291
How did an innocent school trip
end up like this?

194
00:11:33,083 --> 00:11:35,625
Hurry up, Miku.
We're gonna get some food.

195
00:11:35,708 --> 00:11:37,583
Okay. I'll be right there.

196
00:11:37,666 --> 00:11:38,541
[door closes]

197
00:11:39,625 --> 00:11:42,916
[MIKU] If the five of us
really are equal, then...

198
00:11:45,625 --> 00:11:47,291
what am I supposed to do?

199
00:11:49,291 --> 00:11:51,125
Man. I'm so sorry.

200
00:11:52,125 --> 00:11:54,458
I can't believe
I had to get sick now.

201
00:11:54,541 --> 00:11:56,500
Just my luck, right?

202
00:11:56,583 --> 00:11:57,833
You were careless.

203
00:11:57,916 --> 00:11:59,708
Even if it was just
an accident.

204
00:11:59,791 --> 00:12:03,291
Now, stay in bed and think
about what you did wrong.

205
00:12:03,375 --> 00:12:04,875
[ICHIKA]
Harsh!

206
00:12:04,958 --> 00:12:07,958
Well, no reason to stay
in here and watch over me.

207
00:12:08,041 --> 00:12:09,208
Just go skiing.

208
00:12:09,291 --> 00:12:10,750
[ITSUKI]
But...

209
00:12:10,833 --> 00:12:13,208
I'll come and find you guys
when I'm feeling better.

210
00:12:14,750 --> 00:12:18,208
Oh, I know. You're having
trouble facing Futaro now.

211
00:12:18,291 --> 00:12:19,458
[gasps]

212
00:12:20,583 --> 00:12:22,000
[ICHIKA]
You've been tiptoeing around him

213
00:12:22,083 --> 00:12:23,625
since that time at the inn.

214
00:12:24,833 --> 00:12:26,791
Okay, so that was you I saw.

215
00:12:27,791 --> 00:12:29,166
Just three months ago,

216
00:12:30,250 --> 00:12:32,083
when I asked him to help me
with my schoolwork

217
00:12:32,166 --> 00:12:35,333
that day in the cafeteria,
I had no idea.

218
00:12:37,291 --> 00:12:39,500
Things have gotten
so complicated.

219
00:12:41,208 --> 00:12:44,458
Are you sure Futaro's as bad
a guy as you make him out to be?

220
00:12:45,708 --> 00:12:47,625
[ITSUKI] That's not what
I'm talking about!

221
00:12:47,708 --> 00:12:49,791
[shudders]

222
00:12:49,875 --> 00:12:51,000
Think I'll sleep more.

223
00:12:51,083 --> 00:12:53,083
Hey there, Uesugi!

224
00:12:53,166 --> 00:12:55,291
[FUTARO]
Yotsuba!

225
00:12:55,375 --> 00:12:56,791
[YOTSUBA]
You're not getting out of this

226
00:12:56,875 --> 00:12:58,583
just because it's optional.

227
00:12:58,666 --> 00:12:59,875
[FUTARO]
Uh, what?

228
00:12:59,958 --> 00:13:01,791
[YOTSUBA]
Come on, let's hit the slopes!

229
00:13:01,875 --> 00:13:02,916
Yeah!

230
00:13:05,750 --> 00:13:08,875
Whoo! I wanna go
on all of 'em!

231
00:13:08,958 --> 00:13:11,666
And I wanna go back
inside and sleep.

232
00:13:11,750 --> 00:13:13,916
Besides, I've never been
much of a skier.

233
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:16,000
[YOTSUBA] No way.
Sleep is for the weak!

234
00:13:16,083 --> 00:13:17,583
It's okay if you can't ski.

235
00:13:17,666 --> 00:13:20,125
I'll hold your hand
all the way down if you want!

236
00:13:21,250 --> 00:13:23,291
Hey, who wants to study?

237
00:13:24,666 --> 00:13:27,625
Wait, where are
your simpleton sisters?

238
00:13:27,708 --> 00:13:31,333
Ichika's sick in bed today,
so Itsuki's taking care of her.

239
00:13:31,416 --> 00:13:33,416
I guess that's to be expected,

240
00:13:33,500 --> 00:13:35,083
after all that stuff
that happened.

241
00:13:35,166 --> 00:13:36,791
Stuff?

242
00:13:36,875 --> 00:13:39,541
By the way, you can't go around
locking doors without checking.

243
00:13:39,625 --> 00:13:41,833
Huh? That's kinda random.

244
00:13:43,541 --> 00:13:45,625
Well, Nino already
started skiing.

245
00:13:47,291 --> 00:13:48,625
There you are!

246
00:13:50,125 --> 00:13:51,708
[FUTARO]
Who's that?

247
00:13:51,791 --> 00:13:53,166
Miku.

248
00:13:53,250 --> 00:13:54,416
Wow, really?

249
00:13:55,541 --> 00:13:58,208
Man, you're all so hard to tell
apart from just your faces.

250
00:13:58,291 --> 00:14:01,416
♪

251
00:14:01,500 --> 00:14:03,083
Uh...
[grunts]

252
00:14:04,208 --> 00:14:06,000
[giggling]

253
00:14:06,083 --> 00:14:07,416
Not too graceful, huh?

254
00:14:08,708 --> 00:14:09,916
Are you okay? Here.

255
00:14:10,916 --> 00:14:12,125
Uh...

256
00:14:15,541 --> 00:14:17,083
Yeah. I'm all right.

257
00:14:18,916 --> 00:14:20,458
This is great!

258
00:14:20,541 --> 00:14:22,208
I'm always the one who has
to learn stuff from you guys.

259
00:14:22,291 --> 00:14:24,750
But today, I'm doing
all the teaching!

260
00:14:26,916 --> 00:14:29,166
[gasping]

261
00:14:31,333 --> 00:14:33,250
Wow, you kinda suck.

262
00:14:35,041 --> 00:14:37,583
What's up?
It's freezing cold out here!

263
00:14:40,708 --> 00:14:42,583
Who am I talking to now?

264
00:14:42,666 --> 00:14:43,708
[chuckles]

265
00:14:43,791 --> 00:14:46,000
Aw. It's Ichika.

266
00:14:46,083 --> 00:14:47,000
Oh.

267
00:14:48,416 --> 00:14:50,333
Hey, Ichika!

268
00:14:50,416 --> 00:14:52,375
I take it you're feeling better?

269
00:14:55,333 --> 00:14:57,875
Yeah, I'm not
a hundred percent, though.

270
00:14:57,958 --> 00:14:59,583
Okay, so where's Itsuki?

271
00:14:59,666 --> 00:15:02,041
I thought she was
taking care of you.

272
00:15:02,125 --> 00:15:03,708
Nah, she's out here.

273
00:15:03,791 --> 00:15:06,541
She's skiing by herself because
she's not ready to face you.

274
00:15:07,875 --> 00:15:11,291
Ichika! I keep trying
to teach these goofballs,

275
00:15:11,375 --> 00:15:12,750
and they won't listen to me!

276
00:15:12,833 --> 00:15:15,250
Get over it, that's every
single day of my life.

277
00:15:15,333 --> 00:15:17,125
[giggling]

278
00:15:17,208 --> 00:15:19,083
Why don't we make it
more interesting, then?

279
00:15:19,166 --> 00:15:21,083
-Huh?
-[ICHIKA] Let's play tag.

280
00:15:21,166 --> 00:15:23,666
Yotsuba's the best,
so she's "it."

281
00:15:23,750 --> 00:15:26,916
-Sure!
-But what about the others?

282
00:15:27,000 --> 00:15:29,416
Easy, if I find 'em,
then I'll tag 'em!

283
00:15:29,500 --> 00:15:31,958
Okay. One! And two!

284
00:15:32,041 --> 00:15:33,791
-Hey, count slower!
-[YOTSUBA] Three! Four!

285
00:15:33,875 --> 00:15:35,083
-This sucks.
-[YOTSUBA] Five...

286
00:15:35,166 --> 00:15:37,500
I literally just learned
how to go forward.

287
00:15:37,583 --> 00:15:38,916
Wait a sec.

288
00:15:39,000 --> 00:15:41,625
This is my chance
to explain myself to Miku!

289
00:15:41,708 --> 00:15:44,458
Miku! Do you think
we could maybe--

290
00:15:44,541 --> 00:15:46,083
Whoa, slow down!

291
00:15:46,166 --> 00:15:47,375
We need to talk!

292
00:15:48,833 --> 00:15:52,500
Damn. I didn't know I was
dealing with a speed demon here.

293
00:15:54,041 --> 00:15:57,458
[panting]

294
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:00,750
I can't catch a break.

295
00:16:00,833 --> 00:16:02,958
There's something
I've been meaning to ask you.

296
00:16:03,041 --> 00:16:03,875
Ichika.

297
00:16:04,875 --> 00:16:06,791
Did you tell anyone
about last night?

298
00:16:07,833 --> 00:16:08,875
Huh?

299
00:16:11,083 --> 00:16:14,208
I'm thinking
I might quit school.

300
00:16:15,416 --> 00:16:17,583
No, I would never tell.

301
00:16:17,666 --> 00:16:19,000
So that means...

302
00:16:19,083 --> 00:16:20,250
Listen.

303
00:16:20,333 --> 00:16:23,291
Um, how do you stop
this thing?

304
00:16:24,875 --> 00:16:25,916
[ICHIKA]
What?

305
00:16:27,083 --> 00:16:28,416
Aah!

306
00:16:28,500 --> 00:16:30,125
Uesugi!

307
00:16:37,625 --> 00:16:38,625
[screaming]

308
00:16:38,708 --> 00:16:40,375
Ow! Ow! Ow! Ow!

309
00:16:42,916 --> 00:16:43,791
[chuckles]

310
00:16:44,875 --> 00:16:46,166
Yotsuba.

311
00:16:46,250 --> 00:16:48,958
When you teach someone,
you have to be thorough.

312
00:16:49,041 --> 00:16:51,041
[WOMAN]
Are you okay over there?

313
00:16:51,125 --> 00:16:53,125
[MAN]
Dude, are you dead?

314
00:16:53,208 --> 00:16:54,666
[FUTARO]
Nope, perfectly fine!

315
00:16:55,875 --> 00:16:56,791
Don't mind me!

316
00:16:58,000 --> 00:17:00,166
Great, everyone's staring at me.

317
00:17:01,416 --> 00:17:02,583
I don't know if it's because
I gave away

318
00:17:02,666 --> 00:17:04,250
the charm Raiha made for me,

319
00:17:04,333 --> 00:17:07,000
but my luck's been atrocious
since yesterday.

320
00:17:12,041 --> 00:17:13,666
I know this bandage.

321
00:17:14,833 --> 00:17:16,208
Is that you, Kintaro?

322
00:17:17,583 --> 00:17:19,500
It is you, isn't it?

323
00:17:19,583 --> 00:17:21,666
♪

324
00:17:21,750 --> 00:17:23,208
[FUTARO]
Huh? Kintaro?

325
00:17:23,291 --> 00:17:24,666
What kind of dumb name is that?

326
00:17:24,750 --> 00:17:26,208
[NINO]
You jerk!

327
00:17:26,291 --> 00:17:28,625
I think I'd recognize
who I gave this to.

328
00:17:28,708 --> 00:17:31,625
Crap. Now what?

329
00:17:33,750 --> 00:17:35,375
Hey, you can't just run away!

330
00:17:36,416 --> 00:17:38,166
Maybe I should tell her now.

331
00:17:38,250 --> 00:17:41,333
About how I lied at the test
of courage last night.

332
00:17:42,750 --> 00:17:44,666
[NINO]
Come back here!

333
00:17:46,375 --> 00:17:48,625
[FUTARO] What's the best way
to handle this situation?

334
00:17:50,625 --> 00:17:52,208
They've got me cornered!

335
00:17:53,416 --> 00:17:56,250
Ah, looks like
I've finally found you.

336
00:17:56,333 --> 00:17:57,500
Gah!

337
00:17:59,708 --> 00:18:01,041
[NINO]
Wait, Kintaro!

338
00:18:01,125 --> 00:18:03,666
[YOTSUBA]
Uesugi, I'm coming for ya!

339
00:18:07,208 --> 00:18:09,375
Ugh! I'm getting dizzy.

340
00:18:09,458 --> 00:18:11,291
-There you are!
-Ha! Got you!

341
00:18:11,375 --> 00:18:13,166
[BOTH]
Huh?

342
00:18:13,250 --> 00:18:15,791
-Hey, Yotsuba.
-Guess you're "it" now.

343
00:18:15,875 --> 00:18:18,916
Did you happen to see
a blonde guy come this way?

344
00:18:19,000 --> 00:18:21,708
I don't think so.
Have you seen Uesugi?

345
00:18:22,791 --> 00:18:25,666
That's so weird.
I wonder where he is.

346
00:18:28,083 --> 00:18:29,041
Miku?

347
00:18:30,291 --> 00:18:32,875
That was close.
You almost got caught there.

348
00:18:34,833 --> 00:18:36,250
[FUTARO]
Is this an igloo?

349
00:18:36,333 --> 00:18:38,333
Did you make it yourself?

350
00:18:38,416 --> 00:18:41,000
[MIKU]
No. I just found it.

351
00:18:42,041 --> 00:18:43,375
[FUTARO]
I see.

352
00:18:44,750 --> 00:18:46,750
It's pretty cozy in here,
isn't it?

353
00:18:48,083 --> 00:18:49,500
Um, Futaro?

354
00:18:50,958 --> 00:18:54,291
It's cramped.
So, don't move too much.

355
00:18:54,375 --> 00:18:56,500
You're right, I'm sorry.

356
00:18:56,583 --> 00:18:58,333
Okay. I'll get out.

357
00:18:58,416 --> 00:19:01,833
♪

358
00:19:01,916 --> 00:19:03,333
I want you to stay, though.

359
00:19:05,958 --> 00:19:08,875
Ugh. I don't know anymore.

360
00:19:08,958 --> 00:19:09,958
Miku?

361
00:19:10,041 --> 00:19:14,833
♪

362
00:19:14,916 --> 00:19:16,708
[MIKU]
It's just,

363
00:19:16,791 --> 00:19:18,958
well, what if Yotsuba's
still out there?

364
00:19:19,041 --> 00:19:20,666
[FUTARO]
Good point.

365
00:19:20,750 --> 00:19:22,958
I'd better stay
for a little while longer.

366
00:19:23,041 --> 00:19:24,000
[MIKU]
Yeah.

367
00:19:26,208 --> 00:19:28,791
[FUTARO] Where does she get
that endless stamina, anyway?

368
00:19:30,666 --> 00:19:33,625
Of all of you, I'd say
she's the odd one out.

369
00:19:33,708 --> 00:19:36,875
I'm lucky. Without the igloo,
she'd catch me, too.

370
00:19:36,958 --> 00:19:40,166
Why did I let her talk me
into coming out here to ski?

371
00:19:41,166 --> 00:19:42,875
[MIKU]
What is it I'm trying to do?

372
00:19:44,750 --> 00:19:47,875
Okay, so,
how are we gonna escape?

373
00:19:48,875 --> 00:19:49,875
Let's see.

374
00:19:51,208 --> 00:19:52,458
I know.

375
00:19:52,541 --> 00:19:54,250
Yotsuba should have
a handicap.

376
00:19:55,291 --> 00:19:56,500
[FUTARO]
What?

377
00:19:56,583 --> 00:19:58,708
We could make her carry
a bunch of stuff.

378
00:19:58,791 --> 00:20:01,333
That way,
she can't move as fast.

379
00:20:01,416 --> 00:20:03,916
Hah. That might
make it more fun.

380
00:20:04,000 --> 00:20:05,541
Yeah. Great!

381
00:20:05,625 --> 00:20:07,958
But I'm not sure
if I like that idea.

382
00:20:12,666 --> 00:20:15,083
You five were born with
the exact same characteristics

383
00:20:15,166 --> 00:20:16,708
and abilities, right?

384
00:20:16,791 --> 00:20:17,958
You're quintuplets.

385
00:20:19,625 --> 00:20:21,416
That means Yotsuba's
the most athletic one

386
00:20:21,500 --> 00:20:24,083
because she worked hard
to earn that for herself.

387
00:20:26,791 --> 00:20:28,583
I guess that makes sense.

388
00:20:28,666 --> 00:20:31,166
I know this is just
a stupid game of tag, but...

389
00:20:32,666 --> 00:20:34,833
I still don't want
to disrespect her effort.

390
00:20:38,458 --> 00:20:39,833
[MAEDA] You do it because
you want that person

391
00:20:39,916 --> 00:20:40,916
all to yourself.

392
00:20:42,166 --> 00:20:44,291
[ICHIKA] Are you sure
you're okay with that?

393
00:20:44,375 --> 00:20:46,583
[MIKU]
It's fine if he's with Ichika.

394
00:20:46,666 --> 00:20:48,291
[ITSUKI]
What were you guys doing?

395
00:20:48,375 --> 00:20:49,875
[MIKU]
But I can't.

396
00:20:49,958 --> 00:20:52,000
It's only fair
for you to dance with him.

397
00:20:53,500 --> 00:20:55,583
It's good that
you're all equals,

398
00:20:55,666 --> 00:20:57,916
but you can't ignore
the work she's done, either.

399
00:20:58,000 --> 00:20:59,416
♪

400
00:20:59,500 --> 00:21:01,666
You should be fair
instead of equal.

401
00:21:01,750 --> 00:21:05,250
♪

402
00:21:07,750 --> 00:21:08,916
[grunts]

403
00:21:10,166 --> 00:21:11,833
[groans]

404
00:21:11,916 --> 00:21:13,333
Uh, you good?

405
00:21:13,416 --> 00:21:14,791
Yeah, I'm fine.

406
00:21:16,041 --> 00:21:17,583
What is wrong with you?

407
00:21:17,666 --> 00:21:21,416
♪

408
00:21:21,500 --> 00:21:23,208
You're right.
We should be fair.

409
00:21:24,708 --> 00:21:26,375
Huh?

410
00:21:26,458 --> 00:21:29,375
Jeez, what am I sitting here
rambling about?

411
00:21:29,458 --> 00:21:31,666
The heat's making me crazy.

412
00:21:31,750 --> 00:21:33,208
I'll go get some fresh air.

413
00:21:33,291 --> 00:21:37,166
♪

414
00:21:37,250 --> 00:21:38,375
[giggles]

415
00:21:38,458 --> 00:21:41,166
♪

416
00:21:46,041 --> 00:21:48,291
Uesugi?

417
00:21:49,291 --> 00:21:51,750
I'm gonna find you,
no matter what!

418
00:21:51,833 --> 00:21:55,750
♪

419
00:21:56,791 --> 00:21:57,708
[sighs]

420
00:21:57,791 --> 00:21:59,291
Where did he run off to?

421
00:22:01,416 --> 00:22:02,416
Kintaro.

422
00:22:04,500 --> 00:22:07,916
[wind whooshing]

423
00:22:08,000 --> 00:22:13,250
♪

424
00:22:13,333 --> 00:22:15,791
[cell phone buzzing]

425
00:22:20,125 --> 00:22:22,250
Hey there, Miku.
What's going on?

426
00:22:23,458 --> 00:22:25,208
Ichika. Listen.

427
00:22:26,416 --> 00:22:28,166
There's something I need to say.

428
00:24:01,125 --> 00:24:03,583
-[ITSUKI] Futaro.
-[NINO] Get up, Uesugi!

429
00:24:03,666 --> 00:24:05,000
[MIKU]
Futaro.

430
00:24:05,083 --> 00:24:06,458
[YOTSUBA]
Uesugi!

431
00:24:06,541 --> 00:24:08,041
[ICHIKA]
Wake up, Uesugi.

432
00:24:08,125 --> 00:24:10,666
[FUTARO] A-ha! I never
actually met the quintuplets.

433
00:24:10,750 --> 00:24:12,000
This was all a dream!

434
00:24:12,083 --> 00:24:13,708
[QUINTUPLETS]
You know that's not true!

